  <a href="#1" id="1">
   A study published today in the New England Journal of Medicine indicates
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   that an intestinal operation to lower cholesterol of heart attack patients reduced the risk of a second heart attack.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Called a partial ileal bypass, changes the route of the small intestine so that one-third of it is bypassed.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Although lowering the risk of a second heart attack,
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   a major drawback of the procedure is chronic diarrhea, which can last for years.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   Patients also are more prone to kidney stones, gallstones, and intestinal obstructions.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Patients with severe heart damage were not helped by the procedure.
